==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eyas
<hw>Ey`as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.<ets>niais</ets>
fresh from the nest, a derivative fr. L. <ets>nidus</ets> nest. E.
<ets>an eyas</ets> for a <ets>nias</ets>. See <er>Nest</er>, and cf.
<er>Nias</er>, <er>Jashawk</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A
nesting or unfledged bird; in falconry, a young hawk from the nest, not
able to prey for itself.</def> <rj><au>Shak J. H. Walsh</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eyas</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eyas
<hw>Ey"as</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Unfledged, or newly fledged.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like <qex>eyas</qex> hawk up mounts unto the skies,⟦br⟧
His newly budded pinions to assay.</q> <rj><qau>Spebser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

